race.comment: GINGERQUEST (13) is proving to be very hard to catch, and dropped back from a middle distance to a sprint, and won very easily here 9 days ago. If he is in the same mood here, then he can win again. HESKET (6) has not won for some time, but has been improving in his last 3 starts. He is making his track debut on a 7-day backup, and can figure in the top 4 again in an even field. COATACHINO (15) was less than a length from the winner as the favourite when finishing sixth here in her penultimate start, and then was a game third at Narrogin 15 days ago. She cops a wide gate, but stick with her. MAKIN PROPHETS (7) just battled home here last time out, after finishing a solid second on this track before that. He is peaking at the right time and should be included in all combinations. FLYING SOUTH (2) loves it here, and he will be peaking third up from a spell. He cops a wide gate, but can't be left out of any top 4 combinations.
